single-agent Q-learning (Sutton & Barto, 2018, Chapter 6), agent maintains value estimate \(Q(s, )\) state-action pair updates observing reward \(r\) next state \(s'\):\[\begin{equation}
Q(s, ) \leftarrow Q(s, ) + \alpha \left[ r + \gamma \max_{'} Q(s', ') - Q(s, ) \right]
\tag{25.4}
\end{equation}\]repeated matrix games, one “state” (game ), Q-values reduce action values \(Q(a_i)\) player \(\)’s actions. discount factor \(\gamma\) irrelevant stateless setting, update simplifies :\[\begin{equation}
Q_i(a_i) \leftarrow Q_i(a_i) + \alpha \left[ r_i - Q_i(a_i) \right]
\tag{26.1}
\end{equation}\]\(r_i\) payoff player \(\) received playing action \(a_i\) opponent’s (unknown) action.

