MCTS builds search tree incrementally four repeated phases:Selection: Starting root (current game state), traverse tree choosing child nodes according tree policy reaching leaf node. standard tree policy Upper Confidence Bound Trees (UCT):\[\begin{equation}
\text{UCT}(s, ) = \bar{Q}(s, ) + c \sqrt{\frac{\ln N(s)}{N(s, )}}
\tag{28.1}
\end{equation}\]\(\bar{Q}(s, )\) average outcome action \(\) state \(s\), \(N(s)\) visit count state \(s\), \(N(s, )\) visit count action \(\) \(s\), \(c\) exploration constant (typically \(\sqrt{2}\)).Expansion: Add one child nodes tree selected leaf.Expansion: Add one child nodes tree selected leaf.Rollout (simulation): newly expanded node, play complete game using default policy (typically random moves) obtain outcome.Rollout (simulation): newly expanded node, play complete game using default policy (typically random moves) obtain outcome.Backpropagation: Update visit counts value estimates along path expanded node back root.Backpropagation: Update visit counts value estimates along path expanded node back root.fixed number iterations, algorithm selects action root highest visit count — highest average value, visit count robust estimator.

