Regret matching simple online learning algorithm. \(T\) rounds, define cumulative regret action \(\) :\[\begin{equation}
R^T() = \sum_{t=1}^{T} \left[ u(, s^t) - u(^t, s^t) \right]
\tag{29.1}
\end{equation}\]\(u(, s^t)\) payoff playing action \(\) opponent plays \(s^t\), \(^t\) action actually chosen round \(t\). regret matching strategy round \(T+1\) :\[\begin{equation}
\sigma^{T+1}() = \begin{cases}
  \frac{\max(0, R^T())}{\sum_{'} \max(0, R^T('))} & \text{} \sum_{'} \max(0, R^T(')) > 0 \\
  \frac{1}{|\mathcal{}|} & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\tag{24.3}
\end{equation}\]key theorem average strategy \(\bar{\sigma}^T = \frac{1}{T}\sum_{t=1}^{T}\sigma^t\) converges Nash equilibrium two-player zero-sum games.

CFR applies regret matching every information set game tree. iteration:Traverse game tree, computing counterfactual values — expected utility reaching information set, weighted opponent’s probability playing reach .Update cumulative regrets information set.Derive next iteration’s strategy via regret matching.Accumulate strategies averaging.counterfactual value player \(\) information set \(\) :\[\begin{equation}
v_i() = \sum_{z \Z_I} \pi_{-}(z) \cdot \pi_i(z[] \z) \cdot u_i(z)
\tag{29.2}
\end{equation}\]\(Z_I\) set terminal states reachable \(\), \(\pi_{-}(z)\) opponent’s contribution reaching \(z\), \(u_i(z)\) terminal payoff.

