GAN objective minimax game generator \(G\) discriminator \(D\):\[\begin{equation}
\min_G \max_D \; V(G, D) = \mathbb{E}_{x \sim p_{\text{data}}}[\log D(x)] + \mathbb{E}_{z \sim p_z}[\log(1 - D(G(z)))]
\tag{30.1}
\end{equation}\]discriminator \(D(x)\) outputs probability \(x\) came real data distribution \(p_{\text{data}}\) rather generator. generator \(G(z)\) maps random noise \(z\) synthetic data points.Discriminator’s goal: Maximize \(V\) — correctly classify real fake samples.Generator’s goal: Minimize \(V\) — fool discriminator producing samples indistinguishable real data.

fixed generator, optimal discriminator :\[\begin{equation}
D^*(x) = \frac{p_{\text{data}}(x)}{p_{\text{data}}(x) + p_G(x)}
\tag{30.2}
\end{equation}\]\(p_G = p_{\text{data}}\), gives \(D^*(x) = 1/2\) everywhere — equilibrium condition.

